                            <h3>How does the water crisis affect the economy? </h3>
                            <p>Time spent collecting water or seeking a safe place to go accounts for billions of
                                dollars in lost economic opportunities. There are 785 million people in the world who
                                lack access to safe water, and of them, women are generally tasked with water
                                collection. They spend hours, multiple times per day, waiting in long lines at community
                                water kiosks or walking to distant sources like rivers and ponds to find it. This is
                                time spent, and income not earned. An estimated $260 billion is lost globally each year
                                due to lack of basic water and sanitation.</p>
                        </div>
