                            <h3>Empowering families through small, affordable loans </h3>
                            <p>Safe water at home empowers women and their families to explore their income-generating
                                potential. Instead of walking to find water, they have time to earn money by doing
                                things like sewing, farming, and teaching. It is with income from these activities they
                                can break the cycle of poverty.</p>
                            <p>Leneriza lives in the Philippines. Until recently, she didn&#x27;t have access to safe
                                water at home. She purchased water from a vendor for about $60 a month. This amount was
                                more than 20% of her monthly income. A small, affordable loan changed Leneriza&#x27;s
                                life. With the loan she connected her home to the local water utility. Now Leneriza pays
                                a utility bill of about $4.50 a month. <br /></p>
